content.description:
Climb great knobs up and right to a two bolt anchor with quick links.  All bolts for pitch 1.

A second pitch ascends a nice looking crack above the anchor, but I did not do it.
content.location: To the right of One Fine Day

content.description:
Climb straight up the first three bolts then move out left to the fourth bolt of You Insolent Peasant.  It is possible to skip the 4th bolt of You Insolent Peasant and go straight up to the 5th bolt on golden knobs, but a fall here would probably end on the ground.

The climbing is fun and just as good/not much harder than anything on You Insolent Peasant and while the line is more direct, it is a bit of a squeeze job.  The reality is that there are lines all over the place.
content.location: The right starting variation to Insolent Peasant (first straight up line of bolts to the left of the starting corner for Let The Guilty Hang).

content.description:
Fantastic well protected knob climbing going left to a crack after 7th bolt, then back over and up to a nice ledge with a two bolt anchor with rap rings.

May want a piece of gear for crack after 7th bolt, but it is safe without it.

climbs.name: Let the Guilty Hang
climbs.fa: Greg Barnes, Barry Hutten, Liz Carstens, 6/98

content.description:
The obvious roof on the right of Hummingbird wall.  Follow the roof right and over, then climb up and left to join You Insolent Peasant.

Hard but well protected.
content.location: The obvious roof on the right of Hummingbird wall.
